<item>
            <title>[RAVE-1274] Region and region widget permissions in subpages should inherit from the parent page</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/RAVE-1274</link>
                <project id="12311290" key="RAVE">Rave</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue is most notable when using subpages and trying to add, remove, or delete a region widget.  For instance:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;User A creates a page with subpages&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;User A shares the page with User B with editor permissions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;User B goes to the page and tries to move a region widget&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Expected result: The region widget is successfully moved.&lt;br/&gt;
Actual result: And error occurs because the permission evaluator failed for the move&lt;/p&gt;</description>
